据路透社及伊朗当地媒体25日报道，伊朗卫生部副部长伊拉吉·哈利奇被确诊感染新冠肺炎病毒。
Iran's deputy health minister has been diagnosed with the New Crown Pneumonia virus, Reuters and local media reported Wednesday.
路透社称，伊朗卫生部发言人已经确认了这一消息，并表示哈利奇正在接受治疗。
A spokesman for Iran's health ministry confirmed the news and said Haleqi was being treated, Reuters said.
种种现象都显示，伊朗的疫情正在愈演愈烈，而其控制疫情的前景显得步履蹒跚。
All indications are that Iran's epidemic is intensifying and that its prospects for containing it are faltering.
被确诊前一天，哈利奇大汗淋漓出席疫情新闻发布会根据多家外媒和伊朗本地媒体报道，伊拉吉·哈利奇在新冠病毒检测呈阳性后，录制了一段视频。
The day before his diagnosis, he was sweaty at a news conference that, according to foreign and local Iranian media, recorded a video of Eraj Halic after he tested positive for the virus.
视频中他确认自己感染了病毒，但表示“我们会战胜病毒”。
In the video he confirmed that he was infected with the virus, but said "we will defeat the virus."
据伊朗官方媒体报道，此前，哈利奇一直站在伊朗应对疫情的最前线。
He had been at the forefront of Iran's response to the outbreak, according to state media reports.
24日，也就是哈利奇确诊的前一天，他还出席了伊朗国家电视台关于新冠病毒疫情的新闻发布会。
He also attended a news conference on Iran's state television about the new crown virus on Sunday, the day before his diagnosis.
据英国《每日邮报》报道，哈利奇在发布会上一直不断擦汗，并大汗淋漓地向伊朗全国保证，死亡人数比人们担心的要低。
The Daily Mail reported that he had been sweating and sweating at the news conference, assuring Iranians that the death toll was lower than feared.
哈利奇（左）在24日的发布会上频频擦汗 视频截图不仅如此，他当天还否认了美联社援引伊朗半官方媒体伊尔纳通讯社自2月13日至今，伊朗圣城库姆已有50人死于新型冠状病毒感染肺炎的说法。
Khaleqi (left) in a 24-day news conference repeatedly wipe up the video clip, he also denied the Associated Press quoted Iran's semi-official news agency Ilna news agency since February 13, Qom has died of the new coronavirus pneumonia.
伊尔纳通讯社援引库姆当地一名议员艾哈迈德·阿米里亚巴迪·法拉哈尼的话表示，该市已有超过250人被隔离。
The Irna news agency quoted Ahmed Amiliabadi Farrahani, a local councillor in Qom, as saying that more than 250 people in the city had been isolated.
该名官员还表示，50人死亡的最早时间可以追溯到2月13日。
The official also said the earliest history of the 50 deaths dates back to 13 February.
伊朗累计确诊人数增至95例伊朗卫生部公共关系与信息中心主任贾汗普尔25日透露，伊朗新增新冠肺炎确诊34例，新增死亡3例。
Iran confirmed 34 new cases of pneumonia and three new deaths, said Jahanpur, director of public relations and information center of Iran's Ministry of Health.
其中16人来自库姆，9人来自德黑兰。
Of these, 16 were from Qom and 9 from Tehran.
大多数确诊病例都有库姆接触史。
The majority of confirmed cases have a history of exposure to Qom.
截至25日中午，伊朗共确诊新冠肺炎病例95例，死亡15例。
Up to noon on the 25th, Iran confirmed a total of 95 cases of new crown pneumonia, 15 deaths.
24日，中东多个国家确诊从伊朗输入的首例新冠肺炎患者。
24, a number of countries in the Middle East confirmed the importation of the first new crown pneumonia from Iran.
目前，除阿塞拜疆外的6个陆上邻国已经关闭同伊朗的边境。
Currently, six land-based neighbours, with the exception of Azerbaijan, have closed their borders with Iran.
目前，伊朗政府已经关闭了全国大部分地区的学校，并暂停举办足球比赛。
The Iranian government has closed schools in most parts of the country and suspended football matches.
电影院和其他场地的演出也将暂停。
Performance at cinemas and other venues will also be suspended.
伊朗政府已经开始对德黑兰地铁和市内公共交通车辆进行日常卫生处理。
The Iranian government has begun routine sanitary treatment of Tehran's subway and city public transport vehicles.
当地时间23日，伊朗总统鲁哈尼出席内阁会议时表示，德黑兰将动用军事力量控制疫情，尽可能地减小损失。
Iran's President Rowhani said at a cabinet meeting Thursday that Tehran would use military force to contain the outbreak and minimize losses.
另据伊朗Press TV报道，鲁哈尼当天还签发命令，要求伊朗卫生部长纳马基（Saeed Namaki）牵头成立一个国家疫情防控指挥部。
Rouhani also issued an order asking Iran's health minister, Saeed Namaki, to lead the creation of a national command for disease control, press TV reported.
专家担忧中东失守对于伊朗的疫情形势，卫生专家表示了担忧，从各方面条件分析，中东地区都是引发大流行病的“最佳地点”，因为中东地区朝圣者和工人在各国间的流动十分频繁。
Experts worry about the situation in Iran, and health experts have expressed concern that the Middle East is, by all accounts, the "best place" for a pandemic, given the frequency of movements of pilgrims and workers from one country to another.
截至25日，中东有新冠肺炎确诊病例的国家已增至9个：伊朗(95例)、巴林(17例)、阿联酋(13例)、科威特(8例)、以色列(6例)、伊拉克(5例)、阿曼(4例)、阿富汗(1例)、黎巴嫩(1例)。
As at 25, the number of confirmed cases of new crown pneumonia in the Middle East had increased to 9: Iran (95), Bahrain (17), the United Arab Emirates (13), Kuwait (8), Israel (6), Iraq (5), Oman (4), Afghanistan (1) and Lebanon (1).
疫情已导致伊朗、伊拉克、黎巴嫩和阿富汗等国的医院口罩价格一路飙升，其中一些国家的口罩价格高达正常价格的30倍。
The outbreak has led to soaring prices for hospital masks in countries such as Iran, Iraq, Lebanon and Afghanistan, some of which cost as much as 30 times the normal price.
然而，更令专家担心的是，中东国家应对病毒的能力。
What worries experts more, however, is the ability of Middle Eastern countries to deal with the virus.
特别是叙利亚、伊拉克、阿富汗和也门等国的卫生系统因内战或多年动乱而遭致破坏。
In particular, health systems in countries such as Syria, Iraq, Afghanistan and Yemen have been devastated by civil war or years of unrest.
“中东地区国家做好准备了吗？”约旦传染病专家Montaser Bilbisi博士表示。
"Are countries in the Middle East ready?" says Dr. Montaser Bilbisi, a Jordanian expert on infectious diseases.
“坦率地说，我没有（在这里）看到中国或其他国家的防范和警惕程度，甚至连一些个人防护装备都没有准备好。
"Frankly, I don't see [here] the level of preparedness and vigilance on the part of China or other countries, not even some personal protective equipment.
”例如在约旦，他还没有看到一套具有完全防护性的防护服，所以医护人员感染的风险非常高。
In Jordan, for example, he has yet to see a fully protective suit, so the risk of infection is very high for health-care workers.
